1
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:45,880
<i>Back then, my heart was strong</i>

2
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:53,680
<i>As tough as a bar of steel</i>

3
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:58,400
<i>So many men chased after me</i>

4
00:02:58,480 --> 00:03:01,520
<i>But I never paid them any mind</i>

5
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:05,880
<i>Never gave them a thought</i>

6
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:11,320
<i>But now, my heart is starting to weaken</i>

7
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:19,080
<i>From the very first time I saw him</i>
<i>My heart started to waver</i>

8
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:22,920
<i>What is it about this man?</i>

9
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:26,760
<i>Every time I see his face</i>

10
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:31,880
<i>My heart pounds</i>

11
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:36,480
<i>Oh, my heart</i>

12
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:43,320
<i>Why can't you stay composed?</i>

13
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:48,240
<i>Just one teasing smile from him</i>

14
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:50,960
<i>Before I knew it</i>

15
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:53,480
<i>I'd already fallen for him</i>

16
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:54,720
<i>What are you doing, Poona?</i>

17
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:57,560
Uncle Tharin's back!

18
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:59,840
<i>Back then, my heart had never wavered</i>

19
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:13,920
While I was away,

20
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,320
you secretly used my tape
to practice again, didn't you?

21
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:37,080
I've told you many times already.

22
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:39,440
I don't want you becoming a singer.

23
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:45,920
There are plenty of other jobs.
Why not do something else?

24
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,160
Why do you have to be a singer?

25
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,920
Being a singer is dangerous.
Don't you know?

26
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:54,840
Wait.

27
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:56,960
How is being a singer dangerous?

28
00:04:57,040 --> 00:05:00,920
I said no, and that means no.
Don't ask so many questions.

29
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:04,520
You're not going to the music fair
tomorrow night. Got it?

30
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:33,600
Dad.

31
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:38,200
You and Uncle look exactly alike.

32
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:42,120
You're twins.

33
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:49,480
But I think

34
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,920
you wouldn't be as harsh as Uncle.

35
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:58,240
You wouldn't stop me
from becoming a singer like he does.

36
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:01,920
Right, Dad?

37
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,160
This locket

38
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:12,160
represents your parents.

39
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:15,880
Take good care of it.

40
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:21,120
Your mother and father are gone now.

41
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,480
But you're right here, Dad.

42
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,200
Not Dad.

43
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,760
You have to call me Uncle.

44
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:41,600
I'm your father's younger brother.

45
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:47,240
We're twins, so we look alike.

46
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,760
Then where is Dad?

47
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:57,160
Your father and your mother…

48
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:02,520
were killed by evil people.

49
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:12,800
But don't worry, Poona. From now on…

50
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,960
I'll raise you myself.

51
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:25,720
Stay with me, okay?

52
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:33,520
You don't have your father anymore, Poona.

53
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,880
There you are, Poona.

54
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,760
Mama Sroi,

55
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:59,240
Saijai, what is it?

56
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,080
I brought you the rent money.

57
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:03,720
And I made chicken curry
with coconut shoots for you.

58
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:06,560
Thank you.

59
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:10,960
Do you want to go to the Agriculture Fair
tomorrow, Poona?

60
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:12,720
There's going to be a live band too.

61
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:15,160
You could ask to go up and sing.

62
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,040
I'll record a clip for you.

63
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,280
Want to go?

64
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,320
I…

65
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:27,000
I probably can't go.
Uncle Tharin won't let me.

66
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:32,480
Why is he so overprotective of his niece?

67
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:34,960
Half the village is going.

68
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:38,120
Poor Poona.

69
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:40,400
If your father were still here,

70
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:42,640
he wouldn't be as cold-hearted
as your uncle.

71
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:49,560
But if her father were still here,

72
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:54,120
it might be even worse, Auntie.

73
00:08:55,240 --> 00:09:01,400
Don't you remember
what Uncle Phupha did back then?

74
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:05,440
Yeah, that was 20 years ago.

75
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,960
What was it again?

76
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:12,160
I can't remember. Oh, I remember now.

77
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,920
Didn't Uncle Phupha

78
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,320
cheat on his wife

79
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,920
with a singer from the label
named Onanong?

80
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,680
Is that right?

81
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:23,880
Well, well. You're mad?

82
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,560
You're mad, huh?

83
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,440
Poona!

84
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:34,760
Serves you right. That's still too little.

85
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:38,520
Just you wait, Poona.
Do you think you'll always beat me?

86
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:42,920
- Let's go!
- Yes.

87
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,680
Just wait.

88
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:47,880
I'll splash you back.

89
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:19,960
Hello, sir.

90
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:24,440
- Welcome.
- What's the situation?

91
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:27,680
The suspects were transporting drugs
and injured several officers.

92
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:29,200
They're heading toward the border.

93
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:31,360
We'll have to leave this one to you two.

94
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,360
No problem.

95
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,760
Then what are we waiting for?

96
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,960
Let's move, partner.

97
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:56,920
Move!

98
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,080
Shoot at them!

99
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,920
Blow them to pieces!

100
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:04,920
Hey, wait. Why did they stop?

101
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,360
Hey! Manat, run!

102
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:45,720
Hey.

103
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:50,000
You, stay with the truck. The rest of you,

104
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:51,400
follow me!

105
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:04,520
Take him down!

106
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,320
Hey, stop!

107
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:20,640
Stop! I said stop! Stop, or I'll shoot!

108
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,280
Darn.

109
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:25,400
Everyone, search the area!

110
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:33,200
Here, sir.

111
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:35,880
One of them got away.

112
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:38,200
Too bad.

113
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:40,000
Don't cross my path next time.

114
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:45,920
Let him go for now.
The local police will handle the rest.

115
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:57,560
This stuff destroys the nation
and ruins our youth.

116
00:14:58,080 --> 00:15:01,160
Just stopping this much
is already more than worth it.

117
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:08,480
Yes, sir. Understood. Captain.

118
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:11,400
It's Deputy Chief Phuchong.

119
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:20,960
Hello, Deputy Chief.
Captain Chaiya speaking.

120
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:25,520
<i>There's an urgent assignment up north.</i>
<i>I need you two here now.</i>

121
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:28,080
<i>There's a classified mission</i>
<i>in Ban Khok Ta Yu.</i>

122
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:30,800
Yes, sir.

123
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:35,160
What is it?

124
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:39,160
A classified mission in Ban Khok Ta Yu.

125
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:41,320
Sure, partner.

126
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:44,360
As long as it's for the country,
I'll go anywhere.

127
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:47,160
Let's do it, my partner.

128
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:59,480
BAN KHOK TA YU

129
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:02,080
Thank you.

130
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:13,240
If you're in such a hurry,
why not come yesterday?

131
00:16:18,040 --> 00:16:18,880
Excuse me.

132
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,680
Oh, Poona.

133
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:22,640
I'm here for the phone I left for repair.

134
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:24,160
- Just a moment.
- Yes.

135
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:27,120
PHONE REPAIR SERVICE

136
00:16:31,880 --> 00:16:33,160
Here you go.

137
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:36,800
Thank you.

138
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:49,960
Excuse me. This isn't my phone.

139
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:53,360
Could it be…

140
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,160
that young man's?

141
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,440
Where did he go?

142
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:18,480
He walks so fast.
At this rate, he's already in Yala.

143
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:32,400
Hey, you!

144
00:17:33,120 --> 00:17:33,960
Wait!

145
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:44,120
<i>Oh no!</i>

146
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:47,400
<i>We can't end up kissing</i>
<i>like in the dramas!</i>

147
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:06,800
Hey.

148
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:09,000
What's wrong with you?

149
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:16,640
Our phones got switched.

150
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:19,760
Here's yours. The one the shop gave you

151
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:21,880
is actually mine. Give it back.

152
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,480
What?

153
00:18:24,720 --> 00:18:25,760
Here.

154
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:31,200
Check first if that one's really yours.

155
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:38,520
Yeah, it's mine.

156
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:40,560
They're not switched anymore.

157
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:41,400
SATURDAY MARCH 14TH

158
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:45,040
What now?

159
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:49,720
- Hold on.
- No need!

160
00:18:50,320 --> 00:18:51,400
Don't explain anything.

161
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:53,760
I don't want to know.

162
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:55,720
- Well, that's…
- Don't.

163
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:58,120
Go wherever you want.

164
00:18:59,320 --> 00:19:00,480
Hey!

165
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:02,920
My hat.

166
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:52,280
<i>Riding on a motorbike in a short skirt</i>

167
00:19:52,360 --> 00:19:55,920
<i>It's my business, not anyone else's</i>

168
00:19:56,000 --> 00:20:00,800
<i>Talk all you want, you sharp tongue</i>
<i>Are you crazy or what?</i>

169
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:03,480
<i>You nosy people</i>

170
00:20:03,560 --> 00:20:06,400
<i>It's the trend these days, darling</i>

171
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:10,440
<i>It doesn't get in the way</i>
<i>It makes my figure look fabulous</i>

172
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:13,600
<i>Curvy and just right</i>

173
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:18,160
<i>That's what charm looks like</i>

174
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:22,040
<i>If you want to pry</i>
<i>Into other people's lives</i>

175
00:20:22,120 --> 00:20:25,200
<i>Honestly, it's so annoying</i>

176
00:20:25,280 --> 00:20:28,760
<i>May you get a stye in your eye</i>

177
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:32,920
<i>From staring too much</i>
<i>Better watch yourself</i>

178
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:36,240
<i>You boys sure do love to talk</i>

179
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:40,120
<i>I like my freedom</i>

180
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:43,040
<i>In two days, I'll wear it even shorter</i>

181
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:45,360
<i>I've got what it takes</i>

182
00:20:45,440 --> 00:20:47,040
<i>That's why I dare to show it</i>

183
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:49,040
<i>I've got what it takes</i>

184
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:53,760
<i>That's why I dare to show it</i>

185
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:03,320
Come on, everyone.
Give my daughter a round of applause!

186
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:05,040
How is she?

187
00:21:05,120 --> 00:21:06,560
Fabulous!

188
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,320
My daughter, Malee!

189
00:21:12,280 --> 00:21:14,640
Dad, I told you to call me Maria.

190
00:21:15,360 --> 00:21:17,480
Malee is my real name.

191
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:19,400
I told you to call me Maria.

192
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,720
It sounds way more fabulous and iconic.

193
00:21:22,560 --> 00:21:24,640
Alright, Maria it is.

194
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:27,560
Dad, are we done filming yet?

195
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:31,120
Yes, we're done, sweetheart. On camera,

196
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:32,840
you looked absolutely beautiful.

197
00:21:33,520 --> 00:21:36,720
Tonight I'll have my team edit it

198
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,640
and upload it straight to social media.

199
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:41,000
Wow, you're going to be famous.

200
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:44,000
So when do I get to become a singer?

201
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:47,440
You already are one.

202
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:48,840
Signed under the label…

203
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:51,080
Village Head Prueng Music!

204
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:53,880
Yay!

205
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:57,720
You wore your full uniform
just to cheer for your daughter?

206
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,600
I love this uniform.

207
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:03,040
Being village headman

208
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:05,560
has always been my dream.

209
00:22:06,840 --> 00:22:08,560
Don't tell me when you sleep…

210
00:22:08,640 --> 00:22:10,120
- I wear it then too.
- What?

211
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:11,360
I have a meeting.

212
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:14,360
Hey, make sure
the editing's done properly!

213
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:16,280
If your work isn't up to standard,

214
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:18,560
I'll fire you! Out!

215
00:22:19,520 --> 00:22:20,720
In the label,

216
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:22,840
- she's the first and only singer.
- What is this?

217
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:24,240
- Amazing!
- No competition.

218
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:31,440
Hey, Lieutenant.

219
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:34,280
- Which place are you taking me to inspect?
- This one.

220
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:35,920
- This one?
- We're checking it out.

221
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,320
Checking ID cards?

222
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:38,360
- Check out the girls--
- Take it.

223
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:47,240
What's with you, Chaiya?

224
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:49,000
I only asked you to pick up a phone.

225
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:51,280
What's with that sour face?

226
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:53,840
Yeah, exactly.

227
00:22:53,920 --> 00:22:55,040
They're not switched anymore.

228
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:55,880
SATURDAY MARCH 14TH

229
00:22:57,840 --> 00:22:59,520
What now?

230
00:23:02,560 --> 00:23:04,720
- Hold on.
- No need!

231
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:05,880
Don't explain anything.

232
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:08,080
I don't want to know.

233
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:10,720
Did something happen?

234
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:13,560
Exactly. He definitely ran into something.

235
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:15,520
It's nothing.

236
00:23:16,760 --> 00:23:18,880
Nothing? Hey, Chaiya.

237
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:22,360
How about we go scout out
some pubs and bars?

238
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,680
Maybe we'll run into some pretty girls.

239
00:23:25,760 --> 00:23:26,640
No way, Manat.

240
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:30,520
We only go out when necessary.

241
00:23:31,480 --> 00:23:34,560
Under no circumstances
can the people here know who we are.

242
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:35,760
Do you understand?

243
00:23:38,120 --> 00:23:39,760
Understood, boss.

244
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,160
Hey, who's there?

245
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:48,640
It's me, Sergeant Yot.

246
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:51,840
Oh, come on!

247
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:55,480
- I thought it was someone else.
- Just Uncle Sergeant being old.

248
00:23:55,560 --> 00:23:57,640
- Hey!
- Ow!

249
00:23:57,720 --> 00:23:59,360
Why'd you hit me?!

250
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:02,960
Good thing you're here, Uncle.
Were you able to do what we asked?

251
00:24:03,040 --> 00:24:04,400
All taken care of, sir.

252
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:06,520
My lips are sealed tight.

253
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:08,880
None of the local police know

254
00:24:08,960 --> 00:24:10,200
that Captain Chaiya,

255
00:24:10,280 --> 00:24:12,720
Lieutenant Manat, and Sergeant Au

256
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:15,040
are from Central Investigation.

257
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:18,480
Everyone thinks my nephew Manat

258
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:20,280
brought his friends here for a visit.

259
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:23,440
- Very good.
- Uncle Sergeant.

260
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:25,600
Did you come for something?

261
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,200
I did.

262
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:34,320
<i>Our undercover informant in Ban Khok Ta Yu</i>

263
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:37,400
<i>reported that a drug smuggling group</i>

264
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:39,080
<i>will be moving their shipment</i>

265
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:41,760
<i>out of the village today,</i>

266
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:45,000
<i>passing through Nern Samran,</i>
<i>where we're staying.</i>

267
00:24:45,080 --> 00:24:46,800
According to the informant,

268
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:49,400
that should be the van, right,
Sergeant Au?

269
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:52,440
Then let's move.

270
00:24:58,480 --> 00:24:59,320
Sergeant Au!

271
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:01,840
Sarge!

272
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:02,760
Yes, Captain!

273
00:25:02,840 --> 00:25:04,640
Over here.

274
00:25:04,720 --> 00:25:05,720
Let's move.

275
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:08,280
Yes, sir.

276
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:10,280
- Let's move.
- Right. Go!

277
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:13,520
- Sorry, I fell asleep on duty.
- You good?

278
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:14,520
Let's go.

279
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:21,520
- Hey, stop.
- Come on. Just a flat tire.

280
00:25:22,240 --> 00:25:23,520
This should be easy.

281
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:27,240
The battery's dead too.

282
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:29,680
- Just add some air.
- Old man.

283
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:30,920
Huh?

284
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:32,440
What are you doing?

285
00:25:33,040 --> 00:25:34,080
Hey!

286
00:25:37,800 --> 00:25:38,960
Who are you calling old?

287
00:25:39,680 --> 00:25:40,520
You.

288
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:47,320
Still age-shaming people these days?

289
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:49,560
No one says old people anymore.

290
00:25:49,640 --> 00:25:51,520
We say people born a long time ago!

291
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:53,800
- Oh really?
- Yep.

292
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:57,880
So where are you going?

293
00:25:57,960 --> 00:25:59,560
Listen up.

294
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,360
I'm taking this bike…

295
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:03,360
<i>To Ubon, then Sakon Nakhon</i>

296
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:05,560
<i>Then resting in Yala</i>

297
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:08,000
<i>And I'll be back here by evening</i>

298
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:11,600
Why are you two getting into it?

299
00:26:18,840 --> 00:26:20,560
What's going on?

300
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:22,000
This guy's crazy.

301
00:26:22,760 --> 00:26:26,160
- Crazy?
- Just go. Don't piss me off.

302
00:26:26,240 --> 00:26:28,640
- Move!
- Got it.

303
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:30,680
- I said move!
- See you at 4 p.m.

304
00:26:34,320 --> 00:26:35,600
Hey, see that?

305
00:26:36,160 --> 00:26:37,920
Hey! Who are you, old man?

306
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:45,360
- Hey, run!
- Who are they?

307
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:02,000
Retreat, Captain!
There are too many of them.

308
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:04,240
- They're better armed.
- Draw them away first.

309
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:05,280
Go!

310
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:14,600
Why'd they run off so fast?

311
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:16,840
Come on, I thought they had guts.

312
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:19,000
Guess they were scared of us.

313
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:21,440
They're more worried
about what's in the van.

314
00:27:25,720 --> 00:27:26,760
Hey!

315
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:29,880
Chaiya. Chaiya!

316
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:40,120
OUTSTANDING CITIZEN AWARD CEREMONY
BAN KHOK TA YU VILLAGE

317
00:27:44,640 --> 00:27:46,000
What's he doing here?

318
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:53,600
The district officer has arrived.

319
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:56,960
Next is the presentation

320
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:59,840
of the Outstanding Citizen Award

321
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:02,080
for Ban Khok Ta Yu Village.

322
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:06,560
The first award,

323
00:28:06,640 --> 00:28:10,000
the Hometown Gratitude Award, goes to…

324
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:15,080
Kamnan Pong, also known
as Rungrueang Phumthamrong.

325
00:28:15,880 --> 00:28:17,400
A round of applause, please!

326
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:26,720
Please welcome the district officer
to present the award.

327
00:28:36,280 --> 00:28:37,920
KAMNAN RUNGRUEANG PHUMTHAMRONG

328
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:43,920
Thank you, everyone,

329
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:47,120
for taking the time to vote for me.

330
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:50,200
I promise to continue

331
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:51,760
being a role model

332
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:53,720
and to give back to my hometown.

333
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:57,160
But none of this would be possible

334
00:28:57,240 --> 00:28:58,760
without everyone's support,

335
00:28:59,640 --> 00:29:01,480
especially Singha,

336
00:29:03,320 --> 00:29:04,440
Kitti,

337
00:29:04,960 --> 00:29:06,040
and Sornrak.

338
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:15,160
That's Singha.

339
00:29:16,960 --> 00:29:20,120
He owns Darathong Music.
The one behind him is…

340
00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:24,880
Sornrak Darathong, his son

341
00:29:24,960 --> 00:29:26,880
and one of the label's singers.

342
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:33,560
Kamnan Pong is a major backer.

343
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:35,640
He has a good public image

344
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:38,640
because he regularly donates money
to help the villagers.

345
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:41,280
What about the guy sitting next to Singha?

346
00:29:42,560 --> 00:29:43,600
His name is Kitti.

347
00:29:44,200 --> 00:29:46,680
A local politician. He's Singha's friend.

348
00:29:46,760 --> 00:29:48,200
So that's his backing.

349
00:29:54,760 --> 00:29:57,880
DARATHONG

350
00:30:02,560 --> 00:30:03,400
What is it, boss?

351
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:05,400
I placed the order days ago.

352
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:07,560
I already paid the deposit.

353
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:11,520
Why hasn't the delivery been made yet?
Are you trying to cheat me?

354
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:15,720
I'm not cheating you,
but last time, someone interfered.

355
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:17,120
The goods couldn't be delivered.

356
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:18,560
Then when can you deliver it?

357
00:30:19,960 --> 00:30:20,960
Can you do it today?

358
00:30:21,040 --> 00:30:23,880
Today? Sure.

359
00:30:24,920 --> 00:30:27,880
There'll be a crowd
at the Agriculture Fair today.

360
00:30:29,040 --> 00:30:32,080
We can use the chaos to move the goods.
Sounds good, boss?

361
00:30:32,680 --> 00:30:35,840
Fine. I'll send Pleaw to pick it up.

362
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:37,600
You can come get it.

363
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:47,200
Chaiya!

364
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:50,280
What is it, Uncle Sergeant?

365
00:30:50,360 --> 00:30:53,240
I forgot to tell you the other day.

366
00:30:53,320 --> 00:30:54,560
This house's lease has expired.

367
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:56,040
We need to move out fast

368
00:30:56,120 --> 00:30:58,880
before Paula comes to kick us out.

369
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:01,360
Come on, it's just rent.
I'll take care of it.

370
00:31:01,440 --> 00:31:02,520
You?

371
00:31:02,600 --> 00:31:04,960
As if you could afford it!

372
00:31:05,040 --> 00:31:06,600
How much could it be?

373
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:08,000
Well…

374
00:31:08,080 --> 00:31:09,840
Fifteen thousand a month.

375
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:12,080
I've missed three months.

376
00:31:12,160 --> 00:31:14,560
That's 45,000 total.

377
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:15,840
What?

378
00:31:15,920 --> 00:31:17,160
Forty-five thousand!

379
00:31:19,800 --> 00:31:20,640
Sergeant Yot!

380
00:31:20,720 --> 00:31:22,640
She's here.

381
00:31:22,720 --> 00:31:23,680
Sergeant Yot!

382
00:31:23,760 --> 00:31:24,680
What do we do?

383
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:28,120
Don't let me find out
you're hiding in there!

384
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:30,600
You two deal with this first.

385
00:31:30,680 --> 00:31:34,160
Come out by three,
or I'm breaking the door down.

386
00:31:34,240 --> 00:31:36,840
- Go!
- What exactly am I supposed to say?

387
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:38,520
Say whatever you want.

388
00:31:40,320 --> 00:31:42,360
- One!
- Alright, I'm off first.

389
00:31:43,600 --> 00:31:45,360
- Uncle!
- Two!

390
00:31:45,440 --> 00:31:46,440
Go first.

391
00:31:46,520 --> 00:31:49,720
Two and a bit, two and a half!

392
00:31:50,480 --> 00:31:51,480
Three!

393
00:32:21,680 --> 00:32:24,200
I'm Chaiya.

394
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:30,360
Yes, Chaiya. Oh my.

395
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:34,400
I'm Paula, the landlady here.

396
00:32:39,320 --> 00:32:43,240
This is Manat,
Sergeant Yot's nephew and my friend.

397
00:32:44,200 --> 00:32:45,760
Sergeant Yot's nephew?

398
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:49,120
So handsome. Nothing like him. Oh my.

399
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:51,560
Actually, we have something

400
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:54,840
to discuss with you.

401
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:56,560
You want to talk to me?

402
00:32:58,400 --> 00:33:00,960
We would like to keep staying here.

403
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:10,360
As for the rent
Sergeant Yot still owes, we would like to…

404
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:15,160
No need to say anything.
Rent and money aren't the issue.

405
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:17,440
I'm not in a hurry at all.

406
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:20,040
Just pay whenever you have it.

407
00:33:20,920 --> 00:33:23,320
Honestly, after seeing your faces, oh my!

408
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:27,200
I feel like letting you stay for free.
I don't want to charge you anything.

409
00:33:27,280 --> 00:33:28,240
Seriously!

410
00:33:29,360 --> 00:33:31,640
- That won't be necessary.
- How about this?

411
00:33:31,720 --> 00:33:35,680
When you're free, come by my place.

412
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:39,720
We'll sign a new contract, okay?

413
00:33:43,600 --> 00:33:44,680
I'll be waiting.

414
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:49,800
Which one should I choose?
They're both so handsome.

415
00:33:53,880 --> 00:33:54,960
What's with her?

416
00:33:57,280 --> 00:33:59,520
- Count me down.
- Ready, sir?

417
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:01,120
- Ready.
- Five,

418
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:04,080
four, three, two.

419
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:05,920
<i>Everyone, hello!</i>

420
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:08,040
<i>Who's already in the live?</i>
<i>Check in for me.</i>

421
00:34:08,120 --> 00:34:11,679
Guys, today I'm taking you

422
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:13,320
to the Khok Ta Yu Agriculture Fair.

423
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:15,800
<i>There's a small band performing today,</i>

424
00:34:15,880 --> 00:34:18,719
<i>not exactly famous or anything.</i>

425
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:22,480
<i>I just wanted to come</i>
<i>and show them some support</i>

426
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:23,880
<i>as someone in the same industry.</i>

427
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:25,920
Let's go check it out. Come on.

428
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:29,120
There are lots of stalls
along the way too.

429
00:34:29,199 --> 00:34:32,440
<i>Let's check this one out</i>
<i>and see what they're selling. Come on.</i>

430
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:35,400
Auntie.

431
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:37,400
- Hi, Auntie!
- Hello.

432
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:38,679
What are you selling?

433
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:40,560
Meatballs.

434
00:34:40,639 --> 00:34:42,480
Meatballs? Are sales good?

435
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:46,120
Some days are good, but…

436
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:48,520
some days not so good.

437
00:34:49,480 --> 00:34:52,400
Tonight I don't even know

438
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:54,159
if I'll make my money back.

439
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:57,200
Auntie.

440
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:00,680
Auntie.

441
00:35:01,240 --> 00:35:02,760
I feel so bad for you.

442
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:04,560
It's okay.

443
00:35:04,640 --> 00:35:07,080
I know you're a fighter,
but life keeps fighting back.

444
00:35:07,160 --> 00:35:08,240
MEATBALLS

445
00:35:08,320 --> 00:35:09,840
Here, keep this.

446
00:35:10,440 --> 00:35:13,280
Here, 500 baht.
Use it for your business, okay?

447
00:35:21,640 --> 00:35:23,680
Thank you, Mr. Sornrak.

448
00:35:24,880 --> 00:35:25,720
In all my life,

449
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:28,760
no one's ever been this kind to me.

450
00:35:29,880 --> 00:35:31,120
Thank you so much.

451
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:33,120
Auntie, it's okay.

452
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:36,520
We're all Thai, after all.
If I can help, I want to.

453
00:35:36,600 --> 00:35:39,800
Don't cry, Auntie.

454
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,120
No tears.

455
00:35:42,040 --> 00:35:44,920
Could you show the money

456
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:48,480
to the fans on camera?
So they can see you really got it.

457
00:35:48,560 --> 00:35:50,240
Don't cry, okay?

458
00:35:51,080 --> 00:35:52,360
- Here it is.
- Show it to the camera.

459
00:35:52,440 --> 00:35:54,520
Mr. Sornrak really gave it to me.

460
00:35:54,600 --> 00:35:56,880
They're making the drop
somewhere around here tonight.

461
00:35:56,960 --> 00:35:58,040
BAN KHOK TA YU

462
00:35:58,120 --> 00:35:59,920
There's the Agriculture Fair tonight.

463
00:36:02,720 --> 00:36:04,000
At the Agriculture Fair?

464
00:36:04,080 --> 00:36:05,200
Yes, sir.

465
00:36:05,280 --> 00:36:08,440
They wait for events like this
to make the exchange.

466
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:11,880
These bastards
really can be evil anywhere.

467
00:36:12,720 --> 00:36:16,560
They deal in crowded places,
so no one gets suspicious.

468
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:19,800
No wonder the police haven't caught them
after all these years.

469
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:22,760
The police have been after them,
but they never catch them.

470
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:25,000
Even when they do,
it never leads to the big fish.

471
00:36:25,080 --> 00:36:27,920
Is that why Central Investigation

472
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:30,160
assigned this case to you, Captain?

473
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:33,040
Yes. Good timing, Uncle Sergeant.

474
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:35,520
- Please, have a seat.
- Thank you.

475
00:36:38,840 --> 00:36:41,320
The operation the other day
ended in failure.

476
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:43,400
I want to know

477
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:44,760
if they'll recognize my face.

478
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:47,360
You were undercover, weren't you?

479
00:36:47,440 --> 00:36:49,880
They won't recognize you yet.
Right now, they think

480
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:52,520
it was local police in disguise.

481
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:54,680
No one suspects anything.

482
00:36:56,160 --> 00:36:58,640
- And there's something else.
- What is it?

483
00:36:58,720 --> 00:37:00,000
Our informant reported

484
00:37:00,080 --> 00:37:03,280
that a hitman named Pleaw Paknampho

485
00:37:03,360 --> 00:37:05,240
has come up to take a job in this area.

486
00:37:08,080 --> 00:37:09,720
Pleaw Paknampho?

487
00:37:18,080 --> 00:37:19,360
Damn you!

488
00:37:43,360 --> 00:37:45,560
Pleaw, I swear, it wasn't me!

489
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:47,120
This is just a lesson

490
00:37:47,720 --> 00:37:50,000
for a traitorous drug runner like you.

491
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:57,600
You took my drugs and sold them,

492
00:37:57,680 --> 00:37:59,560
then lied to my boss

493
00:37:59,640 --> 00:38:03,400
that the police caught you
and seized the stash. Is that true?

494
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:05,920
No, Pleaw. The police really caught me!

495
00:38:06,600 --> 00:38:07,640
Pleaw.

496
00:38:08,240 --> 00:38:09,840
Say that again.

497
00:38:11,240 --> 00:38:12,520
I give up, Pleaw.

498
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:14,640
Tomorrow I'll bring
all the drugs back to you.

499
00:38:14,720 --> 00:38:16,760
You'd better bring them back fast.

500
00:38:17,520 --> 00:38:19,040
Anyone not involved, stay out of it.

501
00:38:20,040 --> 00:38:22,680
And if anyone runs their mouth,
you'll die by my gun.

502
00:38:31,600 --> 00:38:33,840
That's Pleaw Paknampho,

503
00:38:33,920 --> 00:38:35,560
as ruthless as the rumors say.

504
00:38:42,120 --> 00:38:44,120
Uncle, someone's here to see you.

505
00:38:47,760 --> 00:38:48,600
Who is it?

506
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:50,080
Here she is.

507
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:54,760
- Hello.
- Hello.

508
00:38:54,840 --> 00:38:57,680
- My name is Poona.
- Huh?

509
00:38:57,760 --> 00:38:59,440
- Poona.
- Alright.

510
00:38:59,520 --> 00:39:02,240
Well, I…

511
00:39:02,920 --> 00:39:05,000
You want to apply to be a singer, right?

512
00:39:06,440 --> 00:39:08,120
Yes, I want to be a singer.

513
00:39:08,200 --> 00:39:09,600
Alright.

514
00:39:11,320 --> 00:39:12,360
Can you wash dishes?

515
00:39:13,360 --> 00:39:14,840
- Yes.
- What about making coffee?

516
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:17,320
- Yes.
- And are you afraid of ghosts?

517
00:39:18,120 --> 00:39:19,320
Not at all.

518
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:24,200
Can you carry speakers and run cables?

519
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:27,200
Wow.

520
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:30,160
To become a singer,

521
00:39:30,240 --> 00:39:32,320
do you have to carry speakers
and run cables?

522
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:35,920
In this troupe,
you have to work your way up.

523
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:38,080
You can't skip ahead of everyone else.

524
00:39:38,760 --> 00:39:40,200
See that guy over there?

525
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:42,280
The one carrying the bag of costumes.

526
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:44,280
Next year, he'll wash dishes
and make coffee.

527
00:39:45,280 --> 00:39:46,520
The year after that, he'll do comedy.

528
00:39:47,280 --> 00:39:51,600
And the year after that…

529
00:39:52,320 --> 00:39:53,760
I'll let him sing.

530
00:39:55,840 --> 00:39:58,760
Won't I die first
before becoming a singer?

531
00:39:58,840 --> 00:40:00,240
No, not yet.

532
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:04,600
I was the first one to apply,

533
00:40:04,680 --> 00:40:05,880
and I still haven't sung yet.

534
00:40:11,040 --> 00:40:14,920
So, what do you say?
Do you still want to be a singer?

535
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:15,800
Yes.

536
00:40:17,560 --> 00:40:21,160
Whatever work you give me,
I'll do it all. I won't complain.

537
00:40:34,160 --> 00:40:35,880
KHOK TA YU AGRICULTURE FAIR

538
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:38,560
Who's Poona talking to?

539
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:42,280
Judging by the way he looks,
probably just some roadie.

540
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:45,040
He's too old for that.

541
00:40:45,560 --> 00:40:47,920
Someone that old has to be the band owner.

542
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:50,720
- Really?
- The owner, with a face like that?

543
00:40:50,800 --> 00:40:51,640
Geez!

544
00:40:51,720 --> 00:40:53,600
Then where is the owner?

545
00:40:54,120 --> 00:40:56,600
Follow me. I'll take care of it.

546
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:57,600
Okay.

547
00:41:04,040 --> 00:41:04,880
Hey, you.

548
00:41:06,160 --> 00:41:08,160
Is the band leader here?

549
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:09,800
Go call him for me.

550
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:10,880
What do you need?

551
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:14,040
I'll tell the band leader myself
what I need.

552
00:41:14,120 --> 00:41:15,400
Go call him. Go.

553
00:41:16,960 --> 00:41:18,240
Hurry, go get him!

554
00:41:19,760 --> 00:41:22,120
Boss, someone's here to see you!

555
00:41:22,720 --> 00:41:24,160
Who is it?

556
00:41:25,880 --> 00:41:27,160
What should I tell him?

557
00:41:28,440 --> 00:41:29,280
Tell him

558
00:41:29,360 --> 00:41:32,080
Miss Maria,
Village Head Prueng's daughter,

559
00:41:32,720 --> 00:41:34,680
owner of the high-end coffee shop

560
00:41:34,760 --> 00:41:37,840
in Nern Samran Village, is here.

561
00:41:38,560 --> 00:41:39,680
Go on.

562
00:41:41,280 --> 00:41:42,320
Miss Maria,

563
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:44,640
Village Head Prueng's daughter,
is here to see you!

564
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:51,280
Hello.

565
00:41:54,080 --> 00:41:55,520
I'm Mueangphrai

566
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:56,920
Monsitkhuan,

567
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:58,440
the band leader.

568
00:42:00,480 --> 00:42:02,080
The band leader?!

569
00:42:05,800 --> 00:42:07,680
Hello.

570
00:42:09,680 --> 00:42:11,840
My name is Maria.

571
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:13,320
I'm Poona's close friend.

572
00:42:13,400 --> 00:42:16,520
The two of us are very close.

573
00:42:16,600 --> 00:42:18,680
She came here to apply as a singer, right?

574
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:20,760
Right?

575
00:42:22,080 --> 00:42:23,160
Yes.

576
00:42:25,360 --> 00:42:27,720
I'd like to apply to be a singer too.

577
00:42:27,800 --> 00:42:30,160
I don't just sing.

578
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:32,400
I can sing and dance too.

579
00:42:32,480 --> 00:42:35,920
I can do anything.
Whatever style you want, just name it.

580
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:37,240
Bring it on!

581
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:50,680
We're not taking anyone yet.

582
00:43:09,120 --> 00:43:11,280
This band isn't taking any new singers.

583
00:43:11,360 --> 00:43:15,200
You two, get out. Out!

584
00:43:21,720 --> 00:43:22,960
We don't have the money
to hire singers anymore.

585
00:43:23,040 --> 00:43:26,320
There's barely any work.
Where would we get the money?

586
00:43:28,320 --> 00:43:30,520
Alright. No new singers then.

587
00:43:32,680 --> 00:43:33,880
Excuse me.

588
00:43:34,600 --> 00:43:36,320
Ma'am.

589
00:43:36,400 --> 00:43:37,360
Who are you exactly?

590
00:43:37,440 --> 00:43:41,080
Why do you have so much say,
like you own the band?

591
00:43:44,080 --> 00:43:45,760
That's right. She's the one.

592
00:43:45,840 --> 00:43:49,160
Her name is Wilai,
the real owner of the band.

593
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:51,760
As for me, I'm only the owner in name.

594
00:43:51,840 --> 00:43:53,080
The one who puts up the money,

595
00:43:53,160 --> 00:43:55,240
it's her.

596
00:43:56,920 --> 00:43:57,960
No wonder.

597
00:43:58,040 --> 00:43:59,920
You have such an elegant presence.

598
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:03,160
Even the way you speak sounds musical.

599
00:44:03,240 --> 00:44:04,160
Oh my goodness.

600
00:44:04,240 --> 00:44:06,240
Please take good care of us.

601
00:44:06,320 --> 00:44:08,680
Hello. I'm Sophie.

602
00:44:08,760 --> 00:44:10,520
Hello. Nice to meet you.

603
00:44:10,600 --> 00:44:13,120
Please take good care of me.
My name's Joey.

604
00:44:13,680 --> 00:44:15,840
Hello. My name is Maria,

605
00:44:15,920 --> 00:44:17,760
Village Head Prueng's daughter.

606
00:44:17,840 --> 00:44:20,400
If your band isn't taking new singers yet,

607
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:23,840
can I sing on stage today
to make some content?

608
00:44:23,920 --> 00:44:25,520
- Thank you.
- Sure.

609
00:44:26,600 --> 00:44:27,560
But you have to pay.

610
00:44:28,320 --> 00:44:31,360
What? We have to pay to sing on stage?

611
00:44:32,560 --> 00:44:34,640
Hold on a second.
Normally, singers get paid

612
00:44:34,720 --> 00:44:36,600
- to perform on stage.
- Yeah.

613
00:44:36,680 --> 00:44:38,320
Now not only are we not getting paid,

614
00:44:38,400 --> 00:44:40,240
we have to pay instead?

615
00:44:40,320 --> 00:44:44,680
- Excuse me, but isn't that a bit stingy?
- Exactly.

616
00:44:44,760 --> 00:44:46,000
This is my stage.

617
00:44:46,920 --> 00:44:49,560
I pay the electricity, I pay the workers.

618
00:44:50,840 --> 00:44:52,040
So I have every right.

619
00:44:53,400 --> 00:44:56,480
If you want to go up, you have to pay.

620
00:44:56,560 --> 00:44:59,040
If you don't have money,
then you don't go up.

621
00:45:01,720 --> 00:45:04,600
Fine. Is 2,000 baht enough?

622
00:45:05,240 --> 00:45:08,280
Deal. Then you can sing two songs.

623
00:45:09,280 --> 00:45:11,520
- Two songs!
- What about you?

624
00:45:15,640 --> 00:45:17,520
I don't have any money.

625
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:22,120
I'll excuse myself then.

626
00:45:24,760 --> 00:45:27,400
Today, I'll be up there
performing on stage,

627
00:45:27,480 --> 00:45:28,880
all dressed up.

628
00:45:29,640 --> 00:45:31,200
A poor girl like you

629
00:45:32,200 --> 00:45:34,560
can only stand
in front of the stage and watch.

630
00:45:35,160 --> 00:45:36,360
Sorry, Poona.

631
00:45:37,920 --> 00:45:39,120
Poona?

632
00:45:39,720 --> 00:45:41,680
Wait. Don't go yet.

633
00:45:45,920 --> 00:45:48,440
What's your name again?

634
00:45:49,880 --> 00:45:51,080
Poona.

635
00:45:53,440 --> 00:45:54,720
Poona.

636
00:45:56,920 --> 00:45:58,360
Do you like singing?

637
00:46:00,400 --> 00:46:01,600
Yes.

638
00:46:05,080 --> 00:46:06,160
Why do you like it?

639
00:46:11,400 --> 00:46:12,800
I don't really know.

640
00:46:15,160 --> 00:46:18,360
I just know that
ever since I can remember,

641
00:46:19,200 --> 00:46:21,800
I've loved singing since I was little.

642
00:46:35,440 --> 00:46:38,840
In that case, I'll let you sing for free.

643
00:46:40,400 --> 00:46:41,560
What is this?

644
00:46:42,160 --> 00:46:43,160
What?

645
00:46:43,240 --> 00:46:44,520
That's not fair.

646
00:46:45,040 --> 00:46:46,680
My boss paid to sing.

647
00:46:46,760 --> 00:46:48,320
Why does Poona get to sing for free?

648
00:46:50,720 --> 00:46:52,160
This is my stage.

649
00:46:52,680 --> 00:46:56,440
Whether I let someone sing for free
or make them pay is my business.

650
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:03,920
Tonight,

651
00:47:04,440 --> 00:47:07,200
go up there and sing the song
you think you sing best.

652
00:47:08,440 --> 00:47:09,360
I'll be listening.

653
00:47:11,760 --> 00:47:12,600
Yes.

654
00:47:13,680 --> 00:47:15,000
Thank you so much.

655
00:47:15,080 --> 00:47:17,760
We're leaving! What is this?

656
00:47:18,360 --> 00:47:20,840
She sings for free,
but my boss had to pay.

657
00:47:20,920 --> 00:47:23,000
We're leaving. No need to sing.
Come on, let's go!

658
00:47:23,080 --> 00:47:26,040
Yeah. Better save the money
for grilled meat.

659
00:47:26,120 --> 00:47:26,920
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

660
00:47:27,520 --> 00:47:28,760
I'm not leaving!

661
00:47:30,800 --> 00:47:34,080
If Poona gets to sing, I'm going up too.

662
00:47:50,720 --> 00:47:54,240
<i>Uncle, if Poona wants to be a singer,</i>
<i>just let her be one.</i>

663
00:47:54,320 --> 00:47:55,680
<i>She has talent.</i>

664
00:47:56,320 --> 00:47:57,840
<i>I want to see her become a singer.</i>

665
00:47:58,480 --> 00:48:02,680
<i>Riding on a motorbike in a short skirt</i>
<i>It's my business…</i>

666
00:48:02,760 --> 00:48:05,400
<i>Do you hear them cheering for me, Poona?</i>

667
00:48:05,480 --> 00:48:06,680
Be like me if you can.

668
00:48:07,280 --> 00:48:10,200
<i>A sad country girl waits for him</i>

669
00:48:10,280 --> 00:48:12,720
The apple really doesn't fall far
from the tree.

670
00:48:12,800 --> 00:48:14,280
NEXT EPISODE

671
00:48:16,880 --> 00:48:18,320
What kind of signal are they sending?

672
00:48:19,080 --> 00:48:21,160
Look at them searching for the drugs.

673
00:48:26,280 --> 00:48:27,560
There's a bomb!

674
00:48:33,240 --> 00:48:34,960
Looks like our chance

675
00:48:36,000 --> 00:48:37,640
to get revenge has finally come.

676
00:51:36,280 --> 00:51:39,360
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
